<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h1 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-surface-area">Surface area</h1>



<p id=3D"introduction"></p>



<p>Here you will learn about surface area, including what it is and how to =
calculate it for prisms and pyramids.</p>



<p></p>



<p>Students will first learn about surface area as part of geometry in <spa=
n class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span clas=
s=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1=
998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"=
application/x-tex"> 6 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=3D=
"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut=
" style=3D"height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class=3D"mord">6</span></span></=
span></span></span>th grade.</p>
</div>
</div>



<p id=3D"what-is"></p>



<div class=3D"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-=
layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-what-is-surface-area">What is surf=
ace area?</h2>



<p></p>



<p>The <strong>surface area</strong> is the total area of all of the faces =
of a three-dimensional shape. This includes <strong>prisms and pyramids.</s=
trong> The surface area is always recorded in <strong>square units.</strong=
></p>



<p></p>



<p>Prisms are 3D shapes that have a polygonal base and rectangular faces. A=
 rectangular prism has <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-d=
isplay=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math x=
mlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>6</mn></mr=
ow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> 6 </annotation></semantics><=
/math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D=
"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class=
=3D"mord">6</span></span></span></span></span> <strong>rectangular faces,</=
strong> including <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-displa=
y=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=
=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow><=
annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> 4 </annotation></semantics></mat=
h></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"bas=
e"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class=3D"=
mord">4</span></span></span></span></span> rectangular lateral faces and <s=
pan class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span cl=
ass=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org=
/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=
=3D"application/x-tex"> 2 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span clas=
s=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"s=
trut" style=3D"height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class=3D"mord">2</span></spa=
n></span></span></span> rectangular bases.</p>



<p></p>



<p>For example,</p>



<p></p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img fetchpriority=3D=
"high" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"740" height=3D"476" src=3D"https://third=
