lt=3D"Surface Area image 1 US" class=3D"wp-image-179037" style=3D"width:520=
px;height:undefinedpx"></figure>



<p></p>



<p>Calculate the area of each face and then add them together for the surfa=
ce area of the rectangular prism.</p>



<p></p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img decoding=3D"asyn=
c" width=3D"904" height=3D"229" src=3D"https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-co=
ntent/uploads/2023/06/Surface-Area-image-2-US.png" alt=3D"Surface Area imag=
e 2 US" class=3D"wp-image-179038" style=3D"width:620px;height:undefinedpx">=
</figure>



<p></p>



<p>The surface area of the prism is the sum of the areas. Add each area twi=
ce, since each rectangle appears twice in the prism:</p>



<p></p>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size"><span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" d=
