<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Confusing the base and the height of the prism<br></strong>No m=
atter how the prism is oriented, the height of a prism is always the side l=
ength of the lateral face that does not correspond with the base. The base =
is always the polygon in which the prism is named after.<br>For example,<br=
><figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img decoding=3D"asy=
nc" width=3D"320" class=3D"wp-image-179066" src=3D"https://thirdspacelearni=
ng.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Surface-Area-image-31-US.png" alt=3D"Surf=
ace Area image 31 US"></figure>This is a trapezoidal prism. It has a trapez=
oid as its base. Even though the trapezoids are shown in the front and back=
 position in this image, the trapezoid is still the base and the rectangula=
r sides are the lateral faces.</li>
</ul>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Calculating with different units</strong><br>You need to make s=
ure all measurements are in the same units before calculating surface area.=
<br>For example,<br><figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><=
img decoding=3D"async" width=3D"320" class=3D"wp-image-179057" src=3D"https=
://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Surface-Area-image-22-=
US.png" alt=3D"Surface Area image 22 US"></figure>Before calculating the su=
rface area, the units need to all be the same. Either the <span class=3D"ka=
tex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><=
span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Math=
ML"><semantics><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"app=
lication/x-tex"> cm </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=3D"k=
atex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" =
style=3D"height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class=3D"mord mathnormal">c</span>=
<span class=3D"mord mathnormal">m</span></span></span></span></span> needs =
to be converted to <span class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-displ=
ay=3D"false"><span class=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=
=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>m</m=
i></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex"> mm </annotation></sema=
ntics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span c=
lass=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.4306em;"></span><spa=
n class=3D"mord mathnormal">mm</span></span></span></span></span> or the <s=
pan class=3D"katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display=3D"false"><span cl=
ass=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org=
